inn1.comm: back onto his stumps and pushed into the covers
cuts back off the seam and takes the batsman on the pads as he goes back, heading down the leg side and no appeal
a big stride onto the front foot, again taken on the pad and out into the covers
seams away from the right hander who spars and misses, whipping the bat away after the ball passes but nobody is fooled
angled in, misses and taken on the thigh pad and into the covers
another peach, back of a length, seaming away and the batsman again fends and misses
fired across the left hander who sways back and leaves
back and turned off his hips square ... big gaps on the leg side and an easy single
short, takes the shoulder of the bat ... he had no idea where that went but it skews over the slips and down to third man
wide -  Chattergoon likes them there - but he doesn't time a cut and it thuds into the ground and bobbles nowhere
short but wider, a slash over the slips, quite safe as there's nobody fine catching and four runs in the line of fourth slip
better line and he goes back to defend
pushed to mid-on, Morkel was dozing and he compounded that by throwing at the stumps with the man well in and it's four overthrows
wide and left
slanted across and left
Pollock persisting with the same line, Chattergoon's patience snaps and he has a grope and a miss
straighter, a poke and a miss, no footwork, and he's really being tested this over
wide but overpitched, Chattergoon latches onto it quickly and drives between point and cover, super shot. Pollock yells in anger, all of it with himself
started too wide to tempt
angled in but then holds its line and it beats the bat. One of those that is unplayable
jags into the right hander off the seam, cuts him in two and scoots over the stumps, Boucher scrambles to save the byes
less drama, no shot outside off
half forward, inside edge into his pads and into the covers
snorter, shortish and it spits past the outside edge as he plays back
back, pushed into the off side
outside off, he shoulders arms. The ball swings to leg after passing the bat
wide and left alone
nagging line, he has to think about every delivery
too wide, left alone
back and cut hardish to point
outside off, no shot
short, smacked hard off the back foot but stopped at cover
short, hit back down the ground well over  mid-on
a long way forward and push-driven behind square on the off, third man round to field
tentatively prodded into the off side
right back and watchfully defended
into the groove immediately, the same line angled across the left hander
back, head right over the ball and pushed back to Pollock
well judged from Chattergoon, a good leave
slightly slower - either that or he's already running out of puff - and nurdled gently back to Pollock
slightly wider, cut square and de Villiers at point makes a good stop to his right
back and patted into the leg side
lovely shot,, slightly short outside off and hammered with his front leg in the air through the covers
good recovery from Ntini, straight and he had to settle for a defensive jab abck to the bowler

short, fended to backward point, Parchment sets off and is sent back, the throw misses as the batsman dives, the backing-up fielder fumbles and there is an overthrow but Parchment is still on all fours
more sedate stuff, blocked to cover
big stride forward, almost played on the walk, but Ntini quick to foollow through to prevent the run
again blocked into the pitch, Parchment momentarily thought about a run but once more Ntini quick in the follow through
back and blocked
Chattergoon plays it into the covers
outside off and Chattergoon has had enough, he leans back, slashes but the ball goes over the top of his flailing bat
fuller and driven uppishly over the covers - his head was in the air as he played it -  but safe and it just about has the legs to reach the rope
wow ... that is a great shot ... he comes a stride down the wicket and heaves the ball high over midwicket, really middled and it lands several rows back
straighter, Chattergoon decides he's done enough damage and opts for a sensible block
angled in from wide of the crease, defended to leg and Ntini does the fielding
driven to cover in an inside-out kind of way
onto the front foot and a very loose and swishy drive, the ball straightens and zips past the edge
through a weak push forward, a loud shout from bowler and close fielders, but there was a thick inside edge
short and wide, he leans back and thumps the ball over point. One foot in the air, utterly Caribbean
defended into the off
huge shout for lbw and that looks mighty close this time, rapping him on the back leg, but there were two noises I think
short of a length, he stands tall and punches it out to cover
excellent line on middle stump and shaping back into the left hander. He is forward, defending with gusto
misfield! Cracked on the front foot square of the wicket and Kallis falls to his right - a lumbering, unathletic tumble but he can't save it. Poor effort
good length. Calmly punched out to cover
wide of the off stump and carved down to third man
excellent line on a full length. Chattergoon hurriedly defends
beautifully struck - a free flowing cover drive but he can't bisect the fielders (or fiddlers as I nearly wrote)
on middle-and-leg but a touch shorter. Chattergoon is back, defending
clubbed down the ground. He's so strong on anything too straight, Chattergoon, and he moshed it straight back past Ntini. Excellent timing
nudged out to cover
a thick inside edge. That's the length for Ntini
on his legs, tucked off his hip for a single to midwicket
short and wide of the off stump. Ignored
full, he drives it out to cover
angling into the left-hander's pads, he whips it to mid-on
lovely stroke, just picking this off his pads with a flourish and down to deep square leg
nudged to leg
a swing and a miss outside the off stump
elegantly driven out to extra cover and he sets off for a single. Botha dives well and saves two - excellent stop that
good line and length on off stump which he defends. That's the line for Morkel
a little too full really. He whips it to leg
angling into his legs, he tucks it to leg
flicked through midwicket
Chattergoon crouches into a powerful, well-timed cut but he finds point
the bouncer, and a quick one too - nice and straight. Chattergoon hooks and top-edges it over the wicketkeeper...for four, about a foot inside the boundary
the slower ball this time, he nudges it out to cover
shot of the day! A wonderful off-drive for four. No need to run for those - he timed it perfectly
oh that's a good comeback from Nel, spearing into the off stump and Chattergoon defends
good line and length. He's back, across and defending
wide of the off stump. Left alone
wide of the off stump, he tries to cut but misses
that's a good length, forcing him onto the back foot and he defends cautiously
pushed out to cover
slashed square of the wicket - a forcing stroke off the back foot. And, just to rub more salt into their wounds, it's a no-ball
he steps to leg but that's brilliantly bowled by Morkel, sending it wide and he flings and misses
beaten! Fine ball, bouncing on Chattergoon and passing by his defensive push
sweetly timed to the leg side but Pollock pulls off a crowd-pleasing save
nudged out to the off side
top shot. He just swung through the line and deposited it over long-off for six. A huge hit
pulled with Caribbean enthusiasm (one leg off the ground ala Dessy Haynes) through midwicket
good ball, Chattergoon tries an inventive late-cut - a dabbing sort of cut - but misses
nudged to leg
ooh a swing and a miss outside off - beaten by a touch of movement away from the right hander
cracked on the back foot out to deep extra cover, but he can't time it
tucked off his hip. Excellent running to pick up a single
firmly forward, he pushes this out to de Villiers in the covers
angling into the right hander who defends
beaten by a cracker which holds its line. Parchment didn't have a clue, fishing and missing
firmly pushed out to cover
oh, top shot, striking this through the covers with excellent timing

angled out to the off side and he sets off for a single - but he's in huge trouble here! Dreadful single. Parchment booms "nnnoooooo" almost in slow motion and Chattergoon dives back...and the throw is wide
the slower ball which he chips aerially
forward onto the front foot and punched to cover
elegantly driven, albeit without any power or timing
nudged off his leg and they're going for another mad single - Chattergoon really has to motor, and fortunately he's got a V8 under the bonnet and is home safely
solidly defended on the back foot
what a shot! He has absolutely nailed that down the ground. A stand-and-deliver stroke, thumping it past mid-off for four
what a catch! Is it? It's turned down by the umpire...and in fact it didn't hit his bat. Parchment went on the pull, Boucher dives to his left and pulls off a brilliant save
pushed out to cover
carved down to third man
pushed out to cover
driven down the ground
tossed up on the middle stump. Chattergoon is back, defending
dug out to leg, they sprint a single
Botha appeals, massively, as he beats Parchment with one which spins away and takes the pad
fuller and a touch quicker, it's punched to mid-on
a thumping, excellently timed cut but straight to point
cautiously dabbed out to the off side
forced out to the off side
outside the off stump, again he defends watchfully
back cut down to third man
on middle stump, he defends
tossed up, Parchment punches to leg
drifting down the leg side, he flicks at it but it flies away for four
tossed up outside off and defended
punched back to Botha
goes for a sweep but misses
defended on the front foot
poor ball down the leg side, Chattergoon gets bat on it and it flies away for four
and he's gone! A good length ball wide of the off stump which Chattergoon tries to dab down to third man, but he gets a thin edge through to Boucher
on his legs, Chanderpaul immediately nudges a single
punched out to cover
cautiously defended out to the off side. Good line and length
well bowled! A classical Pollock delivery, cutting away at the last moment and beating Parchment's indecisive forward defensive
fired into his middle stump and defended
on middle stump, he turns it around the corner but there's a short fine leg in place
squeezed out to cover and they sprint through for a single
tossed up, defended
flicked to mid-on
worked wide of mid-on. Ntini at long-on clears up
got him. A fine ball which cuts back into Parchment massively. He's late on it, it raps him quite high on the back leg...and up goes the finger
tucked to leg. A good line on the off stump but he shuffled across and timed it well
it angles into his off stump and he guides it out to cover
ugly shot - Samuels at his worst, there. He stepped to leg and carved it over the top but without timing it...but fortunately, it evaded the fielders
short, Chanderpaul goes to pull but instead just turns it around the corner
angled out to point and he steals a single
fired into his off stump and forced out to the off side
he comes confidently forward, pushing it out defensively
worked to long-on by Chanderpaul who just walks into the stroke
defensively pushed out to cover
flicked to leg
elegantly driven on the front foot but he can't bisect the gap
he tries to pull it but it didn't come onto him quick enough, and the ball balloons to Gibbs at short midwicket
short and searing! That's a vicious bouncer and Bravo is all but decapitated. Instead the ball flicks his shoulder, and that's helpful - if painful - runs
slower ball, tucked into space, and easily back for a couple
rotates the strike again, pushed off the front foot
round the wicket, and that's a loose waft in the general direction of second slip. No contact though
looped onto a leg-stump line, and flicked round the corner
turned to leg again
finds the gap this time, and a jogged single
missed stumping and that was an absolute ripper. Round the wicket to the left-hander, drawn forward by the loop, and beaten by some vicious bite. Boucher couldn't gather either
pushed away to the covers
fuller and straighter, and defended back down the pitch
squeezed down to third man with an open face, and Pollock sprawls in vain on the rope
down on the sweep, and that's a big appeal, but it was outside the line
pushed back down the ground
dabbed down to third man
nudged back to the bowler - trouble here, as they go for a quick single but Nel's throw is wide
a nervous poke to leg
wide of the off stump and left alone
goes for the hook but top-edges it and it's sailing down fine-leg's throat. Or is it? No! It falls short of Morkel's dive
monstrous! A real mow over midwicket - that's the way to play
clang! That's a brilliant shot - a cover drive, hit on the up and timed superbly. Immense power
nudged to leg for a quick single
down the leg side, he tries to turn it through midwicket but gets a leading edge and the ball skies to Boucher's right who takes a simple catch
speared into middle stump, he drives fluently back to the bowler
turned through midwicket
nudged out to the off side and here comes de Villiers, flying in and he picks the ball up and throws down the stumps in one deft move...but the throw is wide
carved down to third man
pulled around the corner
guided out to third man
angled down to third man who pulls off a great save
defended
guided down to third man. Neat stroke
what a catch! A stunning take by the young man in the crowd! A huge pull over midwicket for six and the guy jumps up to take it one-handed high to his right! As good a catch as you'll see
another one! Even sweeter stroke, timing it beautifully down the ground for six

he's gone for another one, but gets a thick outside edge down to third man and Pollock does brilliantly, parrying it before momentum takes him over the boundary...he skips back over, picks up the ball and wings in a throw
good, tight line which he defends
down the ground but it falls short
guided out to cover
down the ground and he swings...and misses
on the pull but he gets a top edge which skies to Morkel
hammered in front of square but the sweeper does well to prevent four
the first wide of the innings which drifts down the leg side
pulled through midwicket
yorked him! Great ball which is too straight and too quick for Lewis
hammers into his pads off a thick inside edge
swung through midwicket
pushed to mid-off who picks it up. They go for a single, throw down the stumps and he's miles short - swift work there
elegantly driven out to long-off
down the leg side, he flicks it to the vacant fine leg but Morkel sprints around the boundary edge and pulls off a brilliant save. Wonderful stuff from Morkel
wide of the off stump, he tries to dab this down to third man but misses
angled down to third man
aerially driven to the deep and they'll get two
full, straight and he squeezes it out to the off side. The throw comes in and parries off the stumps for an overthrow
down the leg side, he tries to pull it but misses
wide of the off stump, he cuts and slices it over the keeper's head for four!
punched to a deepish mid-off for a single...but the throw's wild and they pick up two. Excellent over for West Indies
this pushes him back into his stumps and he defends out to cover
beautiful delivery which squares him up and takes a thick outside edge down to third man
he tries to cut but misses - beaten by the angle into him
played to mid-off, again there is no room for a single - end of a fine over from Nel
full and on the pads, Taylor moves across a bit and clips it over the fielder inside the circle and the ball races away to the fine leg fence
forced away to midwicket and they scamper through for a single, Gibbs fails to hit the stumps and no damage is done
attempted yorker and it ends up as a low fulltoss, Edwards plays it away towards cover, no room for a single there
forced away to deep cover for a single
another yorker gone wrong, this time Taylor smashes the fulltoss to the long on fence
worked away towards third man
forced away wide of the fielder at midwicket
flicked to fine leg
high fulltoss and that is smashed over the midwicket fence
more! in the slot and Taylor punches it straight back down the track - just about beats the man on the fence
this is amazing stuff from Taylor! another fulltoss from Ntini and Taylor hits hard towards long-off and clears Botha in the deep.
pulled away to deep midwicket
and Edwards edges a four to finish the innings. All out slot, ball clips the inside edge and races away to the fine leg fence. 24 off the over - what a finish

inn2.comm: bit wide outside the off stump, left alone

edged and dropped! line and length delivery outside the off stump, bit of away movement and Smith is caught fishing outside the off stump, thick edge and a hard chance is put down by the fielder at second slip
stops a bit and Gibbs ends up with a leading edge
way down the leg side
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Gibbs reads it well and defends it down on the off side
outside the off stump and the ball moved away a fair bit, in the end it was too wide to make Gibbs play at it
closer to the off stump line and Gibbs taps it away on the off side - end of a good first over from Taylor
starts off with a wide delivery outside the off stump, Smiths watchfully plays it away towards cover
forced away down to silly mid-off, not a well timed shot
bit of width offered outside the off stump and Smith plays it down to third man for an easy single
good length and cutting back in, Gibbs is beaten by the movement off the pitch and the ball thuds into the pad
fuller length delivery outside the off stump and Gibbs punches it down to mid-off
forced away towards point, Powell too starts off with a decent over
pitched outside the off stump and angling away. Smith moves across a long way but leaves it through to the keeper
short delivery, too close to cut and Smith taps it down to third man for a single
full and fast - Gibbs gets behind the line and plays it down towards short cover
hits the wrong line and the ball shapes down the leg side
fuller length delivery, close to the off stump line and Gibbs drives it down to mid-off
short of a good length delivery, this one jagged back in and Gibbs tamely played it down to silly mid-on
driven off the front-foot to cover point
fuller length delivery, Smith goes for the drive and the ball rolls away off the inside edge
left alone outside the off stump
quick bouncer, Gibbs thought about the pull but pulls away at the last moment
too good a straight drive and the ball hits the stumps at the other end - what a waste
good length and cutting in, Gibbs stands his ground and defends it down on the off side
cut away at one bounce to the man at backward point
good length delivery outside the off stump, Smith moves across a bit, gets right on top of the line and drives it through covers - here we go
four more! a perfect half-volley, a perfect drive and Smith finds the gap between mid-off and cover
played back to the bowler
clipped away off the pads to the midwicket fence - end of a good over for South Africa
poor line, around the corner and he pulls it for four
good incutter which raps him on the pads
punched on the front foot to mid-off
wide of the off stump, a slower ball, and left alone
slow, loopy and wide
clumped to mid-off
flicked to leg
a wild wide down the leg side...a complete waste and Browne can't save it
Gibbs tucks this off his hip but can't really time it
an ugly stroke played from well back in his crease, without moving his feet at all, and he's quite lucky to get away with it...the ball looping and falling short of mid-on
a forceful clunk from Smith on the front foot
rapped on the pad
pulled around the corner - powerfully struck and placed to perfection. Awful delivery
wow. Wow! He's square cut Powell with so much power that, well...it's absolutely raced to the boundary. Quite brilliant
good comeback, cutting this away from Smith at the last moment
back cut for another four. More timing than power, but the placement was also excellent
calmly nudged to leg
Gibbs comes onto the front foot and guides this out to cover
excellent ball swinging into Gibbs who really plays it poorly. On the back foot he misreads the swing, and the pace too, nudging it to leg
cracked out into the covers
a cracking ball. That's what he's capable of. It angles into Smith before cutting away - beating him all ends up. Beautifully bowled
hammered on the front foot out to mid-off who fields well
worked to leg but he can't time it
smashed through extra cover - this is power cricket at its best. 50 comes up
forced away behind point for an easy single
worked away off the pads to deep midwicket
short delivery, drifting down the leg side and Gibbs ducks under it
take that! slightly short and on the middle and off stump line - Gibbs pulls and pulls WELL. That was six the moment the ball left the bat
And the carnage continues... too full and too wide outside the off stump. Another crunching drive finds the gap between mid-off and cover
cut away off the back-foot to deep point
forced away on the leg side
line and length delivery outside the off stump and Gibbs taps it away towards cover
slower delivery outside the off stump, Gibbs fails to pick it up and goes through with the shot, gets enough bat on it to clear the fielder at mid-on and the ball bounces away to the long-on fence.
worked away on the off side
starts off with a fuller length delivery, Smith continues on his merry way with a fabulous driven past the fielder at mid-off. 191 more to get
187 more to get! horrible line and length from Sammy, on the pads and Smith clips it away to fine leg for yet another boundary - lovely touch shot to bring up his half-century
and gone! short delivery, nothing special there... Smith pulls and finds Chanderpaul at square leg.
left alone outside off
defended on the front foot
steps outside off and Runako Morton pulls off a fine save at midwicket and really makes Kallis run. He had to get his skates on there
a brute of a delivery! That spat up from nowhere and Kallis had to fend that off. He played it brilliantly
wide of the off stump and ignored
gone! A fast, swinging delivery outside the off stump. Kallis tries to drive off the back foot but it flies straight to point - that's a huge wicket for West Indies
good bouncer - good, fast, straight bouncer. de Villiers rightly sways out of the way
on the off stump, nice and straight. de Villiers defends
calmly turned behind square for a single
de Villiers defends this good-length delivery outside the off stump
wide of the off stump and ignored. A little too wide, truth be told
confidently forward onto the front foot, it's defended out to the off side
hammered on the front foot and a brilliant save by point! What a stop that was from Bravo, diving full-length to his right
punched out to cover
ignored outside off
hammered backward of square but straight to backward point. Good grief he nailed that. Gibbs is asleep and they miss out on a single
quality stroke, just flicking this stray with timing and power down to fine leg
middle stump, it's firmly defended
good bouncer which beats de Villiers' hook for pace
down the leg side allowing de Villiers to simply work it through midwicket
on his legs once more. De Villiers steals the strike
wide of the off stump and left alone
left alone outside off
shot! He steps outside off and pummels it through midwicket for four. That was timed beautifully
ignored outside off
again he leaves this wider ball outside the off stump
good, straight delivery
good grief: Gibbs has got a run, flicking this to leg
flicked through midwicket
punched out to the off side
sweetly driven but without power or timing
the bouncer. He ignores it, ducking below
another bouncer which is also left alone
a waste of a delivery, wide of the off stump
left alone
shot. Outside the off stump and pulled with a short-arm jab through midwicket. What timing
fuller and straighter but he drops it out to the off side for a quick single
commandingly driven out to mid-off, but straight to the man there
elegantly punched out to deep extra cover
nice and full, cramping de Villiers for room and he pumps it back to the bowler
onto the front foot and dropped out to the off side - they go for a single but they'll have to hurry. The throw, though, is wide from Devon Smith
ooh he's pulled this...but where's it gone? For six over midwicket! I honestly thought he'd skied that to a fielder but it just flew miles for six
another boundary. Fetched from wide of the off stump and pulled through midwicket with disdain. A horrid delivery
flicked to midwicket
defended firmly on the front foot
wide of the off stump and he tries to dab it down to third man but wisely decided against it
firmly blocked on the front foot to leg
wide of the off stump and left alone
he's back and defending solidly
wide of the off stump, he steps out to the off side and flicks it to leg
left alone once more
onto the front foot, guided down to short third man
he shuffles back and pushes it out to the off side
clumped back to Bravo
the most orthodox of forward defensives
gone! He's bowled him! A wider delivery but it was far too short to be driving. He flayed at it, dragging it onto his leg stump - and only just shaving it, but sufficiently to knock over the bail
left alone outside off
firmly driven out to long-off
Duminy shuffles across his stumps - almost overbalancing in the process - before leaving this wider ball alone
again, ignored
on the off stump, Duminy is right behind it and defending
sweetly driven out to deep extra cover. That is a high class shot indeed
less class this time, budging it back to the bowler
nice little off-cutter which is blocked out. Nicely bowled though
again, de Villiers blocks out this good-length delivery
a touch too full allowing de Villiers to sneak it past the bowler for a quick single
cautiously played back to Bravo
Duminy tries to crack this through the covers but can't time it
a slower ball which he defends
nurdled through midwicket
clattered out to deep extra cover
hmm...risky stroke from Duminy, angling it late past the wicketkeeper and through the vacant slip. Wonderful hands
firmly defended - better line this time
cracked out to that deep extra cover region
left alone
angling into the left hander who drops it out to the off side - cramped for room
very good line and length but Duminy takes a big stride forward, patting it out to the off side and he immediately sets off for a single. Very well run...albeit straight down the pitch
quicker ball which he blocks out
firmly punched back to Bravo, nearly decapitating him. He snaps his neck out of the way and still manages to get a hand on it to stop it. His reflexes are freakish
de Villiers leans back to try and make room for himself and punches it out to Sammy in the covers
flicked to third man
short of a length, Duminy cuts it hard into the ground and they get a single
on middle-and-off, turning away from him and he flicks to leg
tossed up on off stump, drawing Duminy forward into a defensive
pushed out to the off side
but he can't. It's too short and Duminy tucks into a shorter ball on his hips
driven to long-off
nudged to the leg side. Bravo dives across and nearly breaks his legs and fractures a rib with an outrageous dive to save a single
oh yes. A handsome cover drive for four - very similar to how Nasser Hussain used to play them
nudged out to cover
a swing and a miss
angled out to cover
driven to cover
punched out to the off side
Duminy steps forward and tries to defend but is beaten - good length, that, and it very nearly took the outside edge
fuller. Driven
quick feet from Duminy, rocking back and back-cutting this for four. That is some stroke
again it's too short and he cuts this squarer. Jerome Taylor gives chase
neatly flicked through midwicket
a loose stroke from Duminy, trying to drive this on the up but misses. Good line and length
dropped down to the off side
driven out to the off side
he stands tall and punches this out to cover
short, but it doesn't get up on de Villiers who pulls it meekly through midwicket
that kept really low but he dug it out well
driven wide of the fielder at cover
forced away towards midwicket, no room for a single there
bit of width outside the off stump, Duminy has a half hearted tap at it and the ball goes through to the keeper.
cut away behind point
forced away on the leg side
once again eased away off the back-foot for an easy single
inside edge and the ball rolls away down the track
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
close to the off stump line, inside edge and the ball rolls down to fine leg
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven down to mid-off. End of a decent over
short of a length, de Villiers goes back and muddles it back to the bowler
flicked through midwicket for a single. No, they're going for two and the throw is good...but not straight enough, leaving Browne with too much to do
sweetly driven out to cover
nudged to leg
stands tall and punches it out to cover
dabbed to short third man
well wide, driven powerfully off the back foot
pulled to long on
on his toes, Duminy nudges for a zero
short and wide, cut to deep extra cover
elegantly driven to long-on
driven down the ground for his fifty
oh dear. A no-ball. A massive no-ball. How can someone bowling off three paces no-ball?
ah well bowled. de Villiers tries to mow this into the street but it's well tossed up and he's beaten
confidently forward, guiding it out to the off side
a rotten delivery. Too short, too wide and dispatched through the covers with a ferocious cut
driven down the ground
timed down the ground
lovely stroke. A delicate sweep for four
too short allowing Duminy to dab it out to the off side
short and very slow, he bangs it straight to short midwicket
half a shout for lbw but it's well down the leg side
full and straight, he digs it out to mid-on
oh that's close! An excellent length which he drives at and gets a thick inside edge, evading his stumps only marginally
oh dear, that's come out all wrong. Miles wide - it slipped from his hand
orthodoxly driven out to deep extra
struck out to long-off for two
that is a fine stroke - reminiscent of Michael Bevan in his pomp. He comes forward and just guides this square of the wicket for four. Brilliant hands and hand-eye coordination
flicked to leg for a single
bang! Short outside off, de Villiers pulls it commandingly over midwicket for four
and now he square-drives but only for a single
creamed to deep extra cover
full toss banged to long-off

swinging into the right hander who defends

wide of the off stump and left alone
